# NestJS — Controller → Service → Repository

## Layer responsibilities

```
Controller  → HTTP only: parse request, call service, return response. No logic.
Service     → Business logic, throws NestJS exceptions, stateless.
Repository  → Data access only, returns null when not found (never throws).
```

## Controller

```ts
@Post()
@HttpCode(HttpStatus.CREATED)
create(@Body() dto: CreateUserDto, @CurrentUser() user: IAuthUser): Promise<IUser> {
  return this.usersService.create(dto, user.tenantId)
}
```
- No `try/catch` — use exception filters
- Always type return values
- `@HttpCode` explicit for non-200

## Service

```ts
async findOne(id: string): Promise<IUser> {
  const user = await this.repo.findById(id)
  if (!user) throw new NotFoundException(`User ${id} not found`)
  return user
}
```
Built-in exceptions: `NotFoundException` · `ConflictException` · `ForbiddenException` · `BadRequestException`

## Repository

```ts
findById(id: string): Promise<IUser | null> {
  return this.prisma.user.findUnique({ where: { id } })
}
```
Returns `null`, never throws. Service decides what to do with it.

## DTOs

```ts
export class CreateUserDto {
  @IsEmail()
  @Transform(({ value }) => value.toLowerCase().trim())
  email: string

  @IsString()
  @MinLength(2)
  name: string
}

export class UpdateUserDto extends PartialType(CreateUserDto) {}
```

Global ValidationPipe in `main.ts`:
```ts
app.useGlobalPipes(new ValidationPipe({
  whitelist: true,
  forbidNonWhitelisted: true,
  transform: true,
}))
```

## Anti-patterns

| ❌ Don't | ✅ Do |
|---|---|
| Business logic in controller | Move to service |
| `throw NotFoundException` in repository | Return `null`, let service throw |
| Prisma types in controller return type | Use domain interface or DTO |
| Duplicate fields in UpdateDto | `PartialType(CreateDto)` |
